<div type="definition">
<p>SLANTED PART of a LANDSCAPE.</p>
    </div>
<div type="notes">
<div type="old-chinese-criteria">
<p>1. The standard pre-Buddhist word for a slope and perhaps also a hilly landscape more generally is bǎn 阪.</p>
<p>NB: Pō 坡 "slope" is post-Han colloquial.</p>
        </div>
